    <stitle>GENERAL INSTRUMENT ELECTRONIC PROGRAMMABLE SPEEDOMETER/TACHOMETER - DESCRIPTION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>The electronic speedometer/tachometer unit is a microprocessor based instrument. The unit is
                programmable to different tire sizes, axle ratios, and is adaptable to include two-speed axle
                applications. The unit displays engine speed (RPM) based on the number of teeth in the engine flywheel.
                The system as shown in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0803301">Figure 1</hotlnk>, includes the dash unit (speedometer, tachometer, and
                odometer), two input sensors, and vehicle wire harness to connect the system components.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0803301" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0803301" filename="../figg08/g0803301.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Electronic Speedometer/Tachometer System</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. PROGRAMMABLE SPEEDOMETER/TACHOMETER UNIT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TWO SPEED CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. KEY SWITCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. SPEEDOMETER SENSOR UNIT</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. TRANSMISSION GEAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. VEHICLE GROUND</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. ENGINE FLYWHEEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. TACHOMETER SENSOR UNIT</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. OPTIONAL J1708 DATA LINK</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. J1708 SERIAL DATA LINK CONNECTOR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The speedometer/Tachometer Unit mounts in the instrument panel, the road speed sensor mounts in the
                transmission rear bearing cover, and the engine speed sensor mounts in the engine flywheel housing.
            </para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
    </svcsubsec>
